spans.text: to forsake The paths , thy birth and fortune strew with flowers
sober thought restrain thine erring zeal
the dictates of thy early choice
peace with all her comely train , " From starry regions to this clime descends , " Smooths every frown , and softens
charms the world unfolds to fancy's eye
it flaming to each virgin breast
The train of youths arrayed in purest white , Who scattered myrtles as I
with graceful hand , Whose fragrant breath Arabian odour shed : Of meek-eyed novices the circling band , With blooming chaplets wove around their head
Through opening skies no radiant seraph smiles , No saint descends to sooth my soul to rest , No dream of bliss the dreary night beguiles

her ever in the midnight bell , The hollow gale
this terror-shedding grate , My joy-deserted soul
